":"italic_en","text":"a certain animal,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"well known:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L, K:) fem. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, L, Msb:) pl. [of pauc., of the masc.,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aqorudN","text_ar":"اَقْرُدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (L, Msb,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aqoraAdN","text_ar":"اَقْرَادٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (L, K,) and [of mult., of the same,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"quruwdN","text_ar":"قُرُودٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qiradapN","text_ar":"قِرَدَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, L, Msb, K,) and [quasi-pl. n.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaridapN","text_ar":"قَرِدَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K;) and pl. of the fem., (S, L, Msb,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qiradN","text_ar":"قِرَدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, L, Msb, K.) Hence the proverb"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^azonaY mino qirodK","text_ar":"اَزْنَى مِنْ قِرْدٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"More incontinent than an ape"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; because the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qirod","text_ar":"قِرْد"},{"kind":"text","text":"is the most incontinent of animals: (K:) such is generally said to be the meaning of this proverb: (TA:) or (accord. to A'Obeyd, S, L) by"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qrd","text_ar":"قرد"},{"kind":"text","text":"is here meant a man of the tribe of Hudheyl, named Kird, the son of Mo'áwiyeh. (S, L, K.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aibonu Alqirodi","text_ar":"اِبْنُ القِرْدِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hawodal","text_ar":"حَوْدَل"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bnY","text_ar":"بنى"},{"kind":"text","text":".)"}],"source_refs":["TA","L","K","S","Msb"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}